  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 325\u00b0F (165\u00b0C).",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the yogurt, eggs, honey, vanilla, baking soda, and salt until smooth.",
    "Fold in the chopped walnuts and applesauce, if using.",
    "Grease a 9x9 inch baking dish with a light spray of olive oil and pour the batter in, spreading evenly.",
    "Bake for 35\u201340 minutes, or until the top is set and a toothpick comes out clean.",
    "While the casserole bakes, combine 1 tablespoon honey, 1 tablespoon olive oil, and 1 tablespoon water in a small saucepan over medium heat. Stir until the mixture thickens and turns a light amber color, about 3\u20135 minutes. Remove from heat.",
    "Remove the casserole from the oven, drizzle the caramel sauce over the top, and let it set for a few minutes before serving."
  ],
